<p>Donning face masks amid the COVID-19 pandemic, the lovebirds walked hand-in-hand as they meandered through the bustling streets of SoHo.</p>

<p>Loved up: Brooklyn Beckham, 21, and his fiancée Nicola Peltz, 25, continued to look as loved up as ever on Wednesday, when they stepped out for a stroll in New York City</p>

<p>Brooklyn looked casually cool for the outing stepping out in a black ensemble that included a graphic T-shirt, fitted trousers and a baseball cap.</p>

<p>Contrasting his outfit with a pair of white Nike Air Force 1 trainers, the aspiring photographer stayed close to his wife-to-be, who also stepped out in all-black.</p>

<p>American actress Nicola appeared to have coordinated with her British beau, wearing a Balenciaga jacket with skinny jeans and chunky heavy duty boots.</p>

<p>Lovebirds: Donning face masks amid the COVID-19 pandemic, the lovebirds walked hand-in-hand as they meandered through the bustling streets of SoHo</p>

<p>With her golden locks falling beyond her shoulders, the screen star only had eyes for her future husband as they enjoyed their day out together. </p>

<p>Hours earlier, the Nicola and Brooklyn – son of David and Victoria Beckham – posed for a slew of loved-up snaps, which were shared on Instagram.</p>

<p>Cuddling up close, the pair appeared completely smitten, with one intimate snap showing the pair fresh out of the shower. </p>

<p>Nicola shared a black and white snap of the couple, where she could be seen draping her hands across Brooklyn as he sported a face full of shaving cream. </p>

<p>Coordinated: The couple coordinated in black ensembles for their day out in the bustling city</p>

<p>The pair were both wearing only towels, with Brooklyn offering a look at his extensive tattoo collection as he snapped the picture. </p>

<p>Billionaire heiress Nicola captioned the shot, 'love you more everyday', to which Brooklyn gushed, 'I’m the luckiest boy in the world to have you by my side ❤️❤️'.</p>

<p>The pretty blonde then shared another cosy snap of the pair as she called Brooklyn her 'BFF'.   </p>

<p>On Monday, the newly-engaged couple looked smitten as they posed for a short video using the Dua Lipa Instagram filter.</p>

